# 19. けじめ

Toya's Father: Toya, where have you been?
Little Toya: Huh? I was out playing with a friend.
Toya's Father: Stop wasting your time on such trivial things. Now go get ready. You're going to practice late again today.
Little Toya: Okay...
Toya's Father: No. Do it again.
Little Toya: Sorry...
Toya's Father: Again.
Little Toya: But my fingers are tired...
Toya's Father: Doesn't matter. You're not stopping until you can play it.
Little Toya: Okay...
Little Toya: Mom?
Little Toya: Why am I not allowed to go play with my friends? Why do I have to practice piano and violin even on the weekends?
Toya's Mother: You're actually very lucky, Toya. There aren't many people who are able to take private lessons on a daily basis from a top class musician like your father.
Toya's Mother: He taught your brothers as well, and they've all been getting top marks in their competitions.
Toya's Mother: Your father turned down an offer from overseas so he could stay here and teach you, you know. You have to work extra hard to thank him.
Little Toya: .....
Toya: Before I realized it, I started hating everything about music.
Kohane & An: .....
Toya: And to get back at my dad, I quit playing both the piano and the violin.
Toya: To be honest, I would have been fine with anything, as long as he was against it.
Toya: The only reason I started playing non-classical music here was because I thought it would be the best way to make him angry. It was childish of me.
Toya: But Akito, he...
Akito: Now I'm really interested. Hey, how would you like to try singing together?
Akito: This is Ken. He's one of the guys who helped organize RAD WEEKEND!
Akito: One of these days we're going to put on an event as amazing as that one, Toya!
Toya: He taught me all about this town and how to enjoy music again. He even...shared his dream with me.
Toya: Akito was my first true friend.
Toya: But he's always got his sights set straight ahead...
Toya: If I stay with him, I'll just keep him from realizing his dream.
Toya: Even when I'm right next to him, I just can't see the same thing he does.
Kohane: .....
Toya: The only reason I stuck with him for long...is because I was too scared to face the truth.
Toya: In the end, I had the weakest resolve of anyone.
An's Father: .....
Toya: I've been thinking about it for a while now. Having someone like me beside him will only get in his way.
Toya: What Akito really needs are people like you, Shiraishi, Azusawa. People who are serious about chasing their dream of surpassing RAD WEEKEND.
An: What? Us?
Toya: You two are the same as him. You're able to keep moving forward because you believe in the path you chose.
Toya: Your singing showed me that. It also made me realize that I don't have the same resolve.
Toya: That's why I've finally made the decision to stop acting like a child and relying on Akito.
An's Father: .....
Toya: Thank you for everything.
An's Father: Toya, can you do one more thing before you leave?
Toya: Okay...
An's Father: It seems there's still someone here who hasn't accepted your decision. Would you mind talking to them?
Toya: Huh?
Akito: *Huff*... *Huff*...
Toya: Akito?!
An's Father: I think this is my cue to make myself scarce. An, would you keep an eye on things?
An: What? Dad?
Akito: .....
Toya: .....
